times of india_whytrumpstrikeon'narcoter.title: Why Trump strike on 'narcoterrorists' in Caribbean could become a legal headache for the USOn Thursday, the US military launched another strike against what it described as a suspected drug vessel in the Caribbean. It’s unclear whether the survivors were rescued, if they’re receiving medical aid, or whether they are now in US custody — possibly as prisoners of war. The Pentagon has not commented.
